.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-6-4::.
4 different games are played: snooker, monopoly, domino, poker
The people use 4 different means of transport: quad-bike, subway, train, trike
1. the person playing domino is on the left of the person playing poker##1
2. the person playing monopoly is somewhere to the left of the person driving the quad-bike##5
3. the person driving the trike is not the person playing monopoly##6
4. the person driving the trike is somewhere to the right of the person driving the quad-bike##5
5. the person driving the train is on the right of the person driving the subway##1
6. the person playing poker is somewhere to the left of the person driving the trike##5

.:: Answer ::.
|             |     1      |    2     |     3     |    4     |
| Pet         | monopoly | domino | poker     | snooker |
| Transport   | subway     | train    | quad-bike | trike    |

